mongo_graph

Kenny Gorman
http://www.kennygorman.com

Description:
A utility to create RRD graphs using the http interface of MongoDB to fetch data and place it into rrd files
for historical trending information.
  
This is best used with some utility to view the RRD graphs like drraw.

Requirements:
- python 2.4+
- rrdtool with python extensions (http://oss.oetiker.ch/rrdtool/)

Suggested:
- drraw (http://web.taranis.org/drraw/)

Configuration:

Edit the settings.py file for the hosts you want to probe and alter the directories for your system.  See comments
in the file for what the various options do. 

Usage:
./start_graphs.sh
